description:
In 1925, a small CitroÃ«n made history by being the first car to travel right around Australia! What makes this little car, and this event of special interest to The Incredible Journey, is that its owner and driver was Nevill Westwood, a 22-year-old Christian missionary/evangelist from Carmel College, Western Australia. 

Just as the Apostle Paulâs missionary journeys captured the imagination of Nevill Westwood, so Nevillâs missionary journey has captured the imagination of the âThe Incredible Journeyâ team. And so, after 2 years of planning âThe Incredible Journeyâ has big plans to celebrate the 100th anniversary of this pioneering event in 2025 by retracing this incredible journey.

Nevill Westwood had one goal on his incredible journey: Wherever he went, he shared the story of Jesus â Right Around Australia

Our plans include...
â Retracing the route of Nevill Westwood on his missionary trip around Australia in a similar 1923 CitroÃ«n 5CV.
â Re-enact a number of scenes from the original expedition.
â Produce television programs about the event.
â In the true spirit of Nevillâs journey, weâll share the Everlasting Gospel as we go. This will include conducting outreach programs and other forms of evangelism in major cities and in smaller regional centres across rural Australia.

â The CitroÃ«n 5CV 
"Bubsie" The CitroÃ«n was a 1923 5CV model. Nevill bought this car second-hand in Perth and named it Bubsie. He left Perth with his friend, Greg Davies on the 4 August 1925 beginning his journey right around Australia. The original Bubsie can be seen in the National Museum of Australia in Canberra.

â Nevill Westwood and Greg Davies
After becoming a Christian in 1921 at the age of 18, Nevill Westwood enrolled in the missionary course at Darling Range School; known today as Carmel Adventist College. It is here where he met the two-years-older Greg Davies. Nevill responded to a call for missionaries to travel through the northwest of Western Australia to sell a book explaining the prophecies of the Bible. It was entitled âOur Day in the Light of Prophecyâ. He also had a keen interest in automobiles and possessed exceptional mechanical skills, which served him well during his journey. There he had some fascinating experiences and learned a lot about his fellow Australians during the journey.

â What motivated Nevill Westwood to drive Right Around Australia? 
Nevill set out from Bickley in Perth with two goals in mind.
1. To travel the Outback and sell a book called âOur Day in the Light of Bible Prophecyâ.
2. To collect money for Pacific Island countries to help improve education and health. He had hoped to merely reach Darwin if that was even possible; but his incredible journey took him âRight Around Australiaâ.

So join us in 2025 as we retracing this incredible journey!

Visit our website for more details: https://rightaroundaustralia.tij.tv
